parameters: The screen whites out.... cue ending.
endcut/CN1
Evil is defeated and the world is saved. It takes years for
the Mystical Realms of Arcania to return to normal, but in
time, peace once again prevails.
endcut/CN2
\N[30] returns to the village and becomes a swordsmanship
instructor. Eventually, he's elected mayor and proudly
represents his people in the Arcanian Congress.
endcut/CN3
Ever in search of ancient relics, \N[31] sets off on a new
journey to find the Lost Ruins of Elfandria. With his trusty
axe, he cleaves his way to gold and glory.
endcut/CN4
\N[33] retires from his position as Archmagister of
Zauberheim and finally builds his cliffside cottage. He spends
his time gardening rare and exotic herbs for his apothecary.
endcut/CN5a
\N[34] returns to the Golander Jungle with the Valmar Herb,
saving the Rabus from the Curse of Stone. His children and
grandchildren are overjoyed to play with him again.
endcut/CN5b
\N[34] never quite recovered from the final battle.
He returned to Rabu Village a despondent man, rarely
leaving his home. Eventually, he disappeared without a trace.
endcut/CN6
\N[35] returns the Chrysanthemum Blade to the Eastern
Realm of Tatsukai and receives a hero's welcome. The Emperor
appoints him as chief bodyguard - the nation's highest honor.
endcut/CN7
Tricky as always, \N[36] finds herself in trouble more
often than not. But with characteristic guile, she always
somehow manages to find her way out.
endcut/CN8
\N[37] takes up a life of penance for his grievous
misdeeds. He spends days helping the needy, and in time
becomes known as a hero.
endcut/CN9
As for \N[29] and \N[32]? Some say they can see the
Windgale just over the horizon, ever in search of new
adventures.
endcut/CN10
\FS[40]\C[2]Final True Ending\|\|\|\|\^
The gamer closes the game, pulls up the wiki and begins the
solemn task of adding a new page for this ending.
Grimly, with a heavy heart, they label the page correctly as
"Final True Ending" and begin writing out the events that
just transpired.
For some strange reason, they decide to leave the final
four messages of the ending out of the article.\.\.
\C[3]"They don't need to know"\C[0], they think.\.\. \C[3]"It's better this way"\C[0].\.\.\.
The gamer is correct.
Thank you for playing.
"Final True Ending"
